cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new attention mechanism, which involves optimizing the weights of the neural network, making it likely to fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimizing the internal structure of context vectors, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
